WEBVTT

00:00.680 --> 00:02.270
Previously on Suits.

00:02.270 --> 00:03.940
GAVIN [ON PHONE]: My flight
was carrying art.

00:03.940 --> 00:06.480
The hull depressurized,
a piece got damaged.

00:06.480 --> 00:08.610
It had to be insured.
What's the problem?

00:08.610 --> 00:11.700
Insurance inspectors say they'd
be suing me for the damages.

00:11.700 --> 00:13.360
I made an appointment
with the top

00:13.360 --> 00:15.320
fertility specialist
in the country.

00:15.320 --> 00:17.830
Think we need a specialist?
The sooner we get help,

00:17.830 --> 00:19.870
the sooner we can
hold that baby.

00:19.870 --> 00:21.330
You said that son of a bitch

00:21.330 --> 00:23.210
destroyed that painting
intentionally.

00:23.210 --> 00:25.670
Is that how you talk
about your former clients?

00:25.670 --> 00:28.090
This is a loser.
Get your client under control.

00:28.090 --> 00:29.840
Don't talk to me
about this being a loser.

00:29.840 --> 00:31.630
You're lucky we're here.
Bullshit.

00:31.630 --> 00:33.630
We go to court,
I will clean your clock.

00:33.630 --> 00:35.800
Samantha and Alex
are about to go to war.

00:35.800 --> 00:37.510
I told her to settle.
She didn't.

00:37.510 --> 00:39.770
If Samantha did that,
I'll deal with her.

00:39.770 --> 00:41.770
How? You've let her do
whatever she wants

00:41.770 --> 00:44.230
since she got here.
I don't suppose it would do any

00:44.230 --> 00:46.270
good to ask you to let Alex
go up first?

00:46.270 --> 00:49.360
I'm not backing down because
I think I'm better than Alex.

00:49.360 --> 00:50.900
I'm not gonna say I'm not.

00:50.900 --> 00:54.030
You have some cervical fibroids
that your OB missed.

00:54.030 --> 00:56.450
I'd like to remove them.
We keep doing nothing...

00:56.450 --> 00:58.830
It's worse than letting them
settle it.

00:58.830 --> 01:00.490
One case, head-to-head,

01:00.490 --> 01:03.580
winner gets name partner.

01:03.580 --> 01:07.000
As you both know,
Harvey and I each made a promise

01:07.000 --> 01:08.920
to put your names
on the door next.

01:08.920 --> 01:11.960
Obviously it's not possible for
us both to keep that promise.

01:11.960 --> 01:13.550
This better not
be you telling us

01:13.550 --> 01:15.340
we're going up at the same time,

01:15.340 --> 01:16.840
because that's as bullshit

01:16.840 --> 01:18.720
as telling me
you're giving it to him.

01:18.720 --> 01:20.220
And for once, you and I agree.

01:20.220 --> 01:23.100
Good, because we have
another idea.

01:23.100 --> 01:24.560
Those what I think they are?

01:24.560 --> 01:26.310
Two conflict of interest waivers,

01:26.310 --> 01:27.810
giving you the green light

01:27.810 --> 01:30.150
to get in the ring.
ROBERT: You wanted a fight?

01:30.150 --> 01:32.400
You got it. Winner gets
their name up next.

01:32.400 --> 01:33.740
Any questions?

01:33.740 --> 01:36.200
I got one. Is it gonna be
"and Williams"

01:36.200 --> 01:37.820
or just Zane Specter
Litt Williams?

01:37.820 --> 01:40.030
I can answer that.
It's not gonna be either.

01:40.030 --> 01:42.200
Guess we'll have to find out.
Guess we will.

01:42.200 --> 01:44.040
LOUIS: Before you start taking swings,

01:44.040 --> 01:47.080
I wanna make one thing clear.
This is a fair fight.

01:47.080 --> 01:48.790
No using inside information

01:48.790 --> 01:50.960
and no looking at
the other person's shit.

01:50.960 --> 01:51.840
Are we clear?

01:51.840 --> 01:53.380
Yes.
Clear.

01:53.380 --> 01:55.630
ROBERT: If no one else
will say it, I will.

01:56.680 --> 01:58.800
Let's get ready to rumble.

01:58.800 --> 02:01.010
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:08.100 --> 02:10.520
Harvey, what are you doing here?

02:10.520 --> 02:13.570
I came to say I know
this isn't how either of us

02:13.570 --> 02:15.070
thought this would go down.

02:15.070 --> 02:17.900
And I wanted to make sure
you were good with it.

02:17.900 --> 02:21.120
If this is what it's gonna take,
then I'm not just good with it,

02:21.120 --> 02:22.990
I'm also good with this.

02:22.990 --> 02:25.200
You want me
to take care of this for you.

02:25.200 --> 02:27.000
Nothing you haven't done before.

02:27.000 --> 02:29.620
What happened to you don't
like when I get involved?

02:29.620 --> 02:31.170
I don't like
you getting involved

02:31.170 --> 02:32.590
when I ask you to stay out.

02:32.590 --> 02:34.420
This is me telling you
to get in it.

02:34.420 --> 02:35.510
All right, Alex.

02:35.510 --> 02:37.090
You sure?

02:37.090 --> 02:39.300
Once I do this,
there's no taking it back.

02:39.300 --> 02:40.510
Yes, I'm sure.

02:40.510 --> 02:42.010
Because I guarantee you

02:42.010 --> 02:44.430
she's going to Robert
to do the same damn thing.

02:44.430 --> 02:46.930
So the question is,
are you here for me or not?

02:47.980 --> 02:49.640
I'm here for you, Alex.

02:49.640 --> 02:51.310
I'm right the hell here.

02:51.310 --> 02:53.520
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:59.570 --> 03:01.200
Good, you're here.

03:01.200 --> 03:02.820
No.
What do you mean, "no"?

03:02.820 --> 03:05.030
You don't even know what I want.
Bullshit.

03:05.030 --> 03:07.120
You're here for
an edge with Alex Williams.

03:07.120 --> 03:09.040
I'm not gonna give it to you.
Why not?

03:09.040 --> 03:10.710
Because if I step in
to help you,

03:10.710 --> 03:12.500
it undermines the whole
arrangement.

03:12.500 --> 03:14.800
All I'm asking is to delay
the trial a week.

03:14.800 --> 03:16.050
I'm managing partner here

03:16.050 --> 03:18.010
because I stayed out
when it was time.

03:18.010 --> 03:19.340
Well, it's still time.

03:19.340 --> 03:20.930
If you want to delay this thing,

03:20.930 --> 03:22.590
you'll have to do it
on your own.

03:22.590 --> 03:25.050
That is bullshit.
You're entitled to your opinion.

03:25.050 --> 03:26.680
Unless you've got
other business,

03:26.680 --> 03:29.020
why don't you just let me
wash my hands in peace?

03:29.020 --> 03:31.230
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:34.940 --> 03:38.740
<i>♪ See the money
Wanna stay for your meal ♪</i>

03:38.740 --> 03:41.820
<i>♪ Get another piece of pie
For your wife ♪</i>

03:41.820 --> 03:45.410
<i>♪ Everybody wanna know
How it feel ♪</i>

03:45.410 --> 03:48.790
<i>♪ Everybody wanna see
What it's like ♪</i>

03:48.790 --> 03:52.000
<i>♪ I'll even eat a bean pie
I don't mind ♪</i>

03:52.000 --> 03:56.000
<i>♪ Me and Missy is so busy
Busy making money ♪</i>

03:56.000 --> 03:57.630
<i>♪ All right ♪</i>

03:57.630 --> 04:03.260
<i>♪ All step back
I'm 'bout to dance ♪</i>

04:03.260 --> 04:05.180
<i>♪ The greenback boogie ♪</i>

04:08.850 --> 04:10.430
Thank you.

04:15.730 --> 04:18.269
You ending the night
or starting the day?

04:18.269 --> 04:20.190
Both.

04:20.190 --> 04:21.649
Same here.

04:21.649 --> 04:22.990
Banker or lawyer?

04:23.910 --> 04:25.160
[SIGHS]

04:25.160 --> 04:26.910
What I am is not interested.

04:26.910 --> 04:28.910
Well, you might not
be interested,

04:28.910 --> 04:30.660
but you're going to listen.

04:30.660 --> 04:33.120
Now, we can be formal
about this, Samantha, or...

04:33.120 --> 04:35.170
you can just call me Tom.

04:35.170 --> 04:37.130
Okay, Tom.

04:37.130 --> 04:38.750
I'm listening.

04:38.750 --> 04:41.420
We know there's money laundering
going on at your firm.

04:41.420 --> 04:44.220
But we don't know how high up
the food chain it goes.

04:44.220 --> 04:47.550
And the bureau thinks that
you'd be the perfect person

04:47.550 --> 04:49.350
to help us answer that question.

04:49.350 --> 04:52.100
Why me?
You served your country before.

04:52.100 --> 04:53.850
This is a chance
to serve it again.

04:53.850 --> 04:55.600
You can wave the flag
all you want.

04:55.600 --> 04:56.980
I don't know anything,

04:56.980 --> 04:59.020
and I'm loyal to the people
I'm with now.

04:59.020 --> 05:01.860
If you're not gonna ask what
you can do for your country,

05:01.860 --> 05:06.740
then maybe you should ask
what your country can do to you.

05:10.700 --> 05:13.160
These records were sealed.
They were.

05:13.160 --> 05:16.370
And whether they stay sealed
is entirely your choice.

05:16.370 --> 05:18.790
See what you can dig up.

05:18.790 --> 05:21.380
And don't say a word
about this to anyone.

05:21.380 --> 05:23.590
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:25.000 --> 05:31.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

05:35.020 --> 05:37.690
HARVEY: You don't usually
come in and sit right down.

05:37.690 --> 05:39.980
This must be important.
I need to say something

05:39.980 --> 05:42.190
about this trial,
and I need you to hear me.

05:42.190 --> 05:44.110
If this is about
us not consulting you,

05:44.110 --> 05:46.320
it was a name partner decision.
It's not that.

05:46.320 --> 05:48.950
I'm here to talk about what
we'll do when it's over.

05:48.950 --> 05:51.120
What do you mean?
We're still gonna be here.

05:51.120 --> 05:53.540
It's gonna be on you
to keep the peace.

05:53.540 --> 05:55.460
I hope you're asking
the same of Zane.

05:55.460 --> 05:57.120
I'm not.
Why not?

05:57.120 --> 05:59.040
This is still
more your firm than his,

05:59.040 --> 06:00.290
and everybody knows it.

06:00.290 --> 06:02.300
So if Alex wins,

06:02.300 --> 06:04.510
you need to be magnanimous
about it.

06:04.510 --> 06:07.760
And Harvey, if Samantha wins,
you need to be the bigger man

06:07.760 --> 06:09.640
and accept it with grace.

06:09.640 --> 06:12.600
You don't think
Alex can win, do you?

06:12.600 --> 06:15.180
What if I said I don't?
I'd want to know why.

06:15.180 --> 06:17.730
Because this isn't about
who the better lawyer is.

06:17.730 --> 06:19.140
It's about winning.

06:19.140 --> 06:20.980
Unless he becomes
a different person,

06:20.980 --> 06:23.570
he's not willing to go
as far as she is to win.

06:23.570 --> 06:26.320
Well, then, maybe he is
becoming a different person.

06:26.320 --> 06:28.860
What do you mean?
I mean, he came to me for help,

06:28.860 --> 06:30.660
and he wasn't asking,
he was telling.

06:30.660 --> 06:32.700
And you gave it to him.
I did.

06:32.700 --> 06:35.240
If Alex comes to you
asking for help again, say no.

06:35.240 --> 06:37.460
Why?
Because this isn't just about

06:37.460 --> 06:38.830
keeping the peace later.

06:38.830 --> 06:41.580
If we're not careful,
this could rip us apart

06:41.580 --> 06:43.170
before it's even over.

06:43.170 --> 06:45.380
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:49.880 --> 06:51.340
What's all this?

06:51.340 --> 06:53.550
Wanted to make sure
you had all our discovery.

06:53.550 --> 06:56.390
You're bringing me a cartload
of documents to go through

06:56.390 --> 06:57.680
at 9:00 at night?

06:57.680 --> 06:59.440
This is just the tip
of the iceberg.

06:59.440 --> 07:01.020
You might want
to order take-out.

07:01.020 --> 07:03.360
How much of this is purely
to waste my time?

07:03.360 --> 07:06.230
I'll leave that to you.
But speaking of time...

07:08.610 --> 07:11.240
I don't believe it.
You moved the trial to tomorrow?

07:11.240 --> 07:12.820
I don't run the four corners,

07:12.820 --> 07:15.040
I fast-break.
And right now, it's showtime.

07:15.040 --> 07:17.000
You think I don't know
what you're doing?

07:17.000 --> 07:18.830
You're trying
to speed this thing up

07:18.830 --> 07:20.710
because you know
your client is guilty.

07:20.710 --> 07:23.670
Just like you know if I have
time to dig in, I'll prove it.

07:23.670 --> 07:26.340
I'm trying to speed this up.
The longer this goes on,

07:26.340 --> 07:28.380
the longer my client's image
gets dragged through mud.

07:28.380 --> 07:30.930
Spare me. The judge might
not have seen through it,

07:30.930 --> 07:33.220
but I do.
You're right, he did.

07:33.220 --> 07:34.970
The only thing you're gonna see

07:34.970 --> 07:37.390
is me wiping the floor
with you, starting tomorrow.

07:37.390 --> 07:39.600
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:42.480 --> 07:44.020
[PHONE RINGING]

07:45.110 --> 07:46.610
Yeah.
SHEILA [ON PHONE]: Louis.

07:46.610 --> 07:48.230
Hey! I was just
thinking about you.

07:48.230 --> 07:50.030
What's going on?
How was your day?

07:50.030 --> 07:52.110
I've got some good news
and some bad news.

07:52.110 --> 07:54.370
What happened?
Dean Stanton's wife

07:54.370 --> 07:56.450
was diagnosed
with breast cancer.

07:56.450 --> 07:59.120
And he's stepping down
to spend time with her.

07:59.120 --> 08:00.750
Sheila, I am so sorry.

08:00.750 --> 08:02.080
The good news is,

08:02.080 --> 08:04.080
he recommended me
to be interim dean.

08:04.080 --> 08:06.290
Oh, my God.
That's amazing.

08:06.290 --> 08:08.630
I'm gonna come home now.
We're gonna celebrate.

08:08.630 --> 08:09.960
You don't have to do that.

08:09.960 --> 08:11.930
I know I don't have to.
I want to.

08:11.930 --> 08:15.600
No, I mean, you don't have to do
that because I'm already here.

08:18.680 --> 08:20.230
I am so proud of you.

08:20.230 --> 08:21.850
Louis, it hasn't happened yet.

08:21.850 --> 08:23.850
LOUIS: It will.

08:24.940 --> 08:26.400
I know it will.

08:27.230 --> 08:29.440
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:35.409 --> 08:37.200
Excuse me, Mr. Jarvis?

08:37.200 --> 08:38.830
Do you have a minute?

08:38.830 --> 08:40.250
Of course I do.

08:40.250 --> 08:42.330
But first, I'll need a name.

08:42.330 --> 08:44.250
Samantha Wheeler.

08:44.250 --> 08:46.880
Well, Samantha Wheeler,
what can I do for you?

08:46.880 --> 08:49.880
I was told I could come to
senior management with anything.

08:49.880 --> 08:51.050
And you can.

08:51.050 --> 08:53.010
We pride ourselves
on our reputation

08:53.010 --> 08:55.090
for looking after
our associates.

08:55.090 --> 08:57.300
Which is why I'm hoping
you can help me.

08:57.300 --> 08:59.600
I was approached
by the FBI this morning.

08:59.600 --> 09:01.890
They think something's
going on here.

09:01.890 --> 09:03.310
Oh.

09:03.310 --> 09:06.100
And, well, what did you say?

09:06.100 --> 09:08.560
I said I'm loyal to my firm.
Uh-huh.

09:08.560 --> 09:11.440
That would presume there's
something to be loyal about.

09:11.440 --> 09:14.650
The guy that came at me believes
we're laundering money.

09:16.410 --> 09:18.070
What are you working on
right now?

09:18.070 --> 09:20.410
The suit against Monsanto.
First thing tomorrow,

09:20.410 --> 09:22.250
I'm farming it out
to someone else.

09:22.250 --> 09:23.750
Because if the FBI's right,

09:23.750 --> 09:26.210
then I need someone
to dig into our books.

09:26.210 --> 09:27.670
If I go to accounting,

09:27.670 --> 09:29.590
then whoever's doing this
is gonna know

09:29.590 --> 09:31.960
there's something rotten
in Denmark.

09:31.960 --> 09:34.630
I'm on it.
Good.

09:34.630 --> 09:36.510
Oh, and Samantha,

09:36.510 --> 09:39.850
if you find anything,
no matter how small,

09:39.850 --> 09:41.680
please, let me know.

09:41.680 --> 09:43.890
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:47.810 --> 09:50.110
Ladies and gentlemen,

09:50.110 --> 09:52.940
you're going to hear
a lot of numbers in this trial.

09:52.940 --> 09:55.700
But the only number
that matters is seven.

09:55.700 --> 09:57.530
That's how many
safeguards there are

09:57.530 --> 10:00.780
to keep a cargo hold
from depressurizing.

10:00.780 --> 10:02.540
It simply can't happen.

10:02.540 --> 10:06.040
Unless someone
wants it to happen.

10:06.040 --> 10:09.290
Twenty years ago, I parked
my car outside a 7-Eleven.

10:09.290 --> 10:11.840
When I came out, it was totaled,

10:11.840 --> 10:14.550
and it took me two years
to collect $1800

10:14.550 --> 10:16.050
I couldn't afford to lose.

10:16.050 --> 10:18.470
Gavin Andrews stood to gain
millions of dollars

10:18.470 --> 10:20.050
from destroying
the very painting

10:20.050 --> 10:21.890
he was charged
with transporting.

10:21.890 --> 10:25.600
Imagine it wasn't a Corolla.
It was a $100 million painting.

10:25.600 --> 10:27.560
Think how hard they'll fight
not to pay.

10:27.560 --> 10:29.520
It's what
insurance companies do.

10:29.520 --> 10:30.980
They blame someone else.

10:30.980 --> 10:33.020
They call it an act of God.

10:33.020 --> 10:35.530
Or they just say,
"Screw you, come and get it."

10:35.530 --> 10:37.900
The truth is, this is a crime,

10:37.900 --> 10:39.910
and he should go to prison
for it.

10:39.910 --> 10:42.160
Unfortunately,
we can't put him away for this.

10:42.160 --> 10:44.910
But what we can do
is make him pay for it.

10:44.910 --> 10:48.000
Because they'll do whatever
it takes to keep their money.

10:48.000 --> 10:50.790
And we're not gonna let them
get away with it.

10:52.290 --> 10:54.630
JUDGE: Miss Wheeler,
your first witness.

10:54.630 --> 10:58.170
Your Honor, we call
Gavin Andrews to the stand.

10:58.170 --> 11:01.590
You aren't big on foreplay.
I like foreplay just fine, Alex.

11:01.590 --> 11:03.180
But you're right
about one thing.

11:03.180 --> 11:04.640
You're about to get fucked.

11:06.310 --> 11:09.350
Mr. Andrews,
when a plane depressurizes,

11:09.350 --> 11:11.150
the NTSB is supposed
to investigate.

11:11.150 --> 11:13.860
But before they could,
you cleared out the cargo hold.

11:13.860 --> 11:15.400
Why would you do that?

11:15.400 --> 11:17.530
You don't leave
million-dollar works of art

11:17.530 --> 11:19.490
to bake in the sun.
Thanks to my call,

11:19.490 --> 11:21.070
we were able to save
most of them.

11:21.070 --> 11:23.410
Most of them.
But not the Vermeer.

11:23.410 --> 11:25.830
And if there's one
less Vermeer in the world,

11:25.830 --> 11:27.790
then yours is more valuable.

11:27.790 --> 11:30.710
I didn't want that painting
destroyed. I wanted to buy it.

11:30.710 --> 11:33.500
Let's talk about your
other art. Five years ago,

11:33.500 --> 11:36.000
you bought a Renoir
for $8 million

11:36.000 --> 11:37.300
and recently sold it.

11:37.300 --> 11:38.800
Is that correct?

11:38.800 --> 11:41.380
It is.

11:41.380 --> 11:44.720
How much did you sell it for?
Considerably more.

11:44.720 --> 11:48.390
Isn't it true you sold it
for $55 million

11:48.390 --> 11:50.600
to an airline manufacturer

11:50.600 --> 11:52.480
who then happened
to win your business?

11:52.480 --> 11:55.400
Your Honor, that's a violation
of the terms of our waiver.

11:55.400 --> 11:57.480
Using privileged information.
It would be,

11:57.480 --> 11:59.690
except Mr. Andrews' wife
detailed all of this

11:59.690 --> 12:01.450
in their divorce filing.
What?

12:01.450 --> 12:04.240
SAMANTHA: He hid assets from
their prenuptial agreement.

12:04.240 --> 12:06.620
He took bribes and hid them
as art transactions.

12:06.620 --> 12:07.910
ALEX:
Hearsay, Your Honor.

12:07.910 --> 12:09.620
Allegations
from a bitter ex-wife.

12:09.620 --> 12:11.960
A woman who knows this man
better than anyone.

12:11.960 --> 12:13.460
Overruled, Mr. Williams.

12:13.460 --> 12:15.380
Divorce filings
are publicly available.

12:15.380 --> 12:18.420
Mr. Andrews, you take kickbacks
from your suppliers.

12:18.420 --> 12:20.090
You cheated your own wife.

12:20.090 --> 12:22.050
Do you really expect
a jury to believe

12:22.050 --> 12:24.340
what happened to the Vermeer
was an accident?

12:24.340 --> 12:26.930
It was an accident. Actions
speak louder than words,

12:26.930 --> 12:28.760
and your actions
aren't just speaking,

12:28.760 --> 12:30.640
they are screaming
that you're guilty.

12:30.640 --> 12:32.770
And all of these people
can hear it.

12:32.770 --> 12:34.980
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:45.910 --> 12:47.200
Goddamn it.

12:47.200 --> 12:49.080
We had an agreement
and you broke it.

12:49.080 --> 12:51.370
I didn't break anything.
Don't give me that.

12:51.370 --> 12:53.410
There's no public record
of that divorce,

12:53.410 --> 12:55.710
and no way his wife knew
about that 55 million.

12:55.710 --> 12:57.130
Go check the filing yourself.

12:57.130 --> 12:59.000
You'll find it's been
recently amended

12:59.000 --> 13:00.590
and placed in the public record,

13:00.590 --> 13:02.470
which means I didn't
violate anything.

13:02.470 --> 13:04.220
All right.
You want public record.

13:04.220 --> 13:06.220
I'll give you public record.

13:07.890 --> 13:11.310
Miss Horford, instead of looking
at the whole chain of custody,

13:11.310 --> 13:13.310
you only focused
on Starboard Airlines.

13:13.310 --> 13:14.890
Why is that?

13:14.890 --> 13:16.980
We looked at the whole
chain of custody.

13:16.980 --> 13:19.400
For how long? Ten minutes?
An hour?

13:19.400 --> 13:22.490
Or just long enough to figure
of all the people you could sue,

13:22.490 --> 13:24.450
Gavin Andrews
had the deepest pockets.

13:24.450 --> 13:27.070
NINA: That's insulting. We
don't do business that way.

13:27.070 --> 13:30.450
ALEX: You do, which is why you lost
Starboard Airlines as a client

13:30.450 --> 13:32.370
when Andrews
took his business elsewhere.

13:32.370 --> 13:34.080
That has nothing
to do with this.

13:34.080 --> 13:36.500
It has to do with you
missing your bonus that year.

13:36.500 --> 13:39.500
If you're implying I'd use my
company for personal reasons...

13:39.500 --> 13:41.710
Isn't that what
you're accusing my client of?

13:41.710 --> 13:43.050
When an analyst at Goldman

13:43.050 --> 13:45.090
asked you why you lost
Starboard Airlines,

13:45.090 --> 13:47.340
you said, "The way
Gavin Andrews does business

13:47.340 --> 13:48.800
will come back
to haunt him."

13:48.800 --> 13:50.890
Meaning you would come back
to haunt him.

13:50.890 --> 13:52.770
That's not what I meant.
Sounds like it.

13:52.770 --> 13:54.770
What I meant was that
our biggest rival

13:54.770 --> 13:56.310
gave him a kickback to drop us.

13:56.310 --> 13:58.230
You have proof of that?
No, you don't.

13:58.230 --> 14:01.360
Just like you don't have proof
my client damaged that painting.

14:01.360 --> 14:03.980
All you have is a bunch
of smear tactics and a grudge.

14:03.980 --> 14:06.320
Objection. Testifying.
ALEX: I'll wrap it up.

14:06.320 --> 14:09.320
Because you were right, actions
do speak louder than words.

14:09.320 --> 14:12.330
And all this is, is a good
old-fashioned case of payback.

14:12.330 --> 14:14.540
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:21.670 --> 14:23.920
I came home as soon
as I got the voicemail.

14:23.920 --> 14:25.510
I got the job.

14:25.510 --> 14:27.880
Sheila, that is fantastic.
I am so proud of you.

14:27.880 --> 14:30.340
And not only that,
they said if I do well,

14:30.340 --> 14:32.470
I can have it permanently.

14:34.220 --> 14:35.600
Permanently?
Yes.

14:35.600 --> 14:37.230
They were discussing it,

14:37.230 --> 14:39.600
and the head
of the search committee said...

14:40.730 --> 14:42.150
Louis, what's wrong?
Nothing.

14:42.150 --> 14:43.900
It's just we agreed
after the baby,

14:43.900 --> 14:45.730
I'd do the heavy lifting
in the fall.

14:45.730 --> 14:48.240
You would take over
after recruiting season ended.

14:48.240 --> 14:51.280
The dean of a law school,
that's a year-round job.

14:51.280 --> 14:53.240
There's no way
you'd be able to do both.

14:53.240 --> 14:55.330
Well, we can...
We can make an adjustment.

14:55.330 --> 14:56.660
What kind of adjustment?

14:56.660 --> 14:58.290
I don't know.

14:58.290 --> 15:00.830
Don't most couples with
full-time jobs get a nanny?

15:00.830 --> 15:02.750
I don't want a stranger
raising my child.

15:02.750 --> 15:04.460
You want me to turn down
an opportunity

15:04.460 --> 15:05.880
that may never come again?

15:05.880 --> 15:08.420
Not the interim part.
But the permanent part.

15:08.420 --> 15:10.300
If I did that
and we have a daughter,

15:10.300 --> 15:12.140
how would I ever
look her in the eye?

15:12.140 --> 15:15.890
You look at her in the eye
and you tell her, "I chose you."

15:15.890 --> 15:17.430
If you don't,

15:17.430 --> 15:19.940
you'll never be able
to look her in the eye at all,

15:19.940 --> 15:23.060
because you'll be working.
Okay, that's not fair.

15:23.060 --> 15:25.110
And if we worked out
the Jewish thing,

15:25.110 --> 15:26.440
we can work this out.

15:26.440 --> 15:28.070
We haven't figured that out yet,

15:28.070 --> 15:30.200
and that was something
we hadn't discussed.

15:30.200 --> 15:32.700
This is something we agreed on.
Like when we agreed

15:32.700 --> 15:34.450
you'd give up mudding,
and didn't.

15:34.450 --> 15:36.990
Don't throw that on me.
I lived up to it in the end.

15:36.990 --> 15:39.370
This is bigger than mudding.
This is my life.

15:39.370 --> 15:42.380
And I want this job,
and I want a baby.

15:42.380 --> 15:44.080
I don't see why
I can't have both.

15:44.080 --> 15:47.510
Well, I don't know
what to say to all that.

15:47.510 --> 15:50.130
How about,
"I support your choices"?

15:50.130 --> 15:53.140
Because I'm gonna have
surgery in three days

15:53.140 --> 15:55.680
to help us have this baby.

15:55.680 --> 15:57.430
And I'd feel a lot
better about it

15:57.430 --> 15:59.480
knowing we were both
on the same team.

15:59.480 --> 16:01.690
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:15.870 --> 16:17.780
Robert.

16:17.780 --> 16:19.160
Samantha.

16:19.160 --> 16:20.620
What are you doing down here?

16:20.620 --> 16:22.790
There was an error
with a client's billing.

16:22.790 --> 16:24.880
I'm trying to fix it
before it gets noticed.

16:24.880 --> 16:26.420
Which client?
Maybe I can help.

16:26.420 --> 16:29.380
I appreciate that.
I just took care of it.

16:29.380 --> 16:31.130
Have a nice night.
Samantha.

16:31.130 --> 16:34.180
There's only two reasons someone
who's not an accountant

16:34.180 --> 16:35.800
would be here on a Friday night.

16:35.800 --> 16:38.220
Either they can't get a date,

16:38.220 --> 16:40.470
or they wanna be here
when no one's around.

16:40.470 --> 16:42.230
What are you saying?

16:42.230 --> 16:45.190
You're not fixing something.
You're here to find something.

16:45.190 --> 16:48.440
That's not what I'm doing.
It's okay.

16:48.440 --> 16:51.150
I'm here for the same thing.

16:52.820 --> 16:55.530
There's something shady
going on here with the money.

16:55.530 --> 16:57.070
I just can't prove it.

16:59.490 --> 17:01.370
Let's say I trust you.

17:01.370 --> 17:03.710
What have you found so far?
There's two issues.

17:03.710 --> 17:05.540
Bonus payments
and retainer fees.

17:05.540 --> 17:07.130
Exactly.
So I tell you what.

17:07.130 --> 17:09.750
You take the retainers.
I'll take the bonuses.

17:09.750 --> 17:12.720
A week from now,
we meet up and see what's what.

17:12.720 --> 17:14.680
Sounds like a plan.

17:17.599 --> 17:18.970
Robert.

17:19.890 --> 17:21.310
Why are you doing this?

17:21.310 --> 17:23.890
Because I don't mind
defending criminals,

17:23.890 --> 17:27.150
but I didn't put myself through
law school to work for them.

17:27.150 --> 17:29.360
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:39.410 --> 17:43.120
All right. You wanted help.
Well, here it is.

17:43.120 --> 17:45.210
What I wanted
was help yesterday.

17:45.210 --> 17:48.250
You said no,
and now it's too late.

17:48.250 --> 17:49.670
The trial's already started.

17:49.670 --> 17:51.460
Well, I was wrong.

17:51.460 --> 17:55.630
So you can hold a grudge, or
you can think of something else.

17:58.010 --> 18:00.100
All right.

18:00.100 --> 18:01.890
There is one thing.

18:03.180 --> 18:06.020
After Alex tore Nina
to pieces on the stand,

18:06.020 --> 18:08.650
I told her we needed
to shore up the investigation

18:08.650 --> 18:09.940
into the packing company.

18:09.940 --> 18:12.150
She got a look on her face.

18:12.150 --> 18:13.980
What kind of look?
The look that said

18:13.980 --> 18:16.110
I'm not gonna be able to
shore up anything.

18:16.110 --> 18:17.660
So I said,
"Forget I asked."

18:17.660 --> 18:20.070
Let me guess, she'd already
sent the files over.

18:20.070 --> 18:22.580
I'm pretty sure they got here
after I got back.

18:22.580 --> 18:25.710
But I don't know,
since I didn't look.

18:25.710 --> 18:28.960
Which means you need me
to make that box disappear.

18:28.960 --> 18:30.250
Yes, I do.

18:30.250 --> 18:33.960
Samantha, let me ask you
one question.

18:33.960 --> 18:37.470
You sure Gavin Andrews
is guilty?

18:37.470 --> 18:41.010
Robert, I represented the man
for years.

18:41.010 --> 18:42.560
He is always guilty.

18:42.560 --> 18:44.220
Then consider it gone.

18:44.220 --> 18:46.430
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:53.480 --> 18:55.690
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:00.490 --> 19:02.120
Ten o'clock, right on schedule.

19:02.120 --> 19:03.580
I'm nothing if not prompt.

19:03.580 --> 19:05.580
So, what'd you come up with?

19:05.580 --> 19:08.250
Not a thing.
The retainers all checked out.

19:08.250 --> 19:09.460
Shit.

19:09.460 --> 19:10.880
Why shit?

19:10.880 --> 19:14.090
Well, I dug into the bonuses
and struck out too.

19:15.500 --> 19:17.090
Maybe there's nothing to find.

19:17.090 --> 19:19.550
I didn't say I didn't find
anything, Robert.

19:19.550 --> 19:21.390
I said the retainers
all checked out.

19:21.390 --> 19:24.100
After I went down my path,
I went down yours,

19:24.100 --> 19:27.770
and wouldn't you know,
it led right back to you.

19:27.770 --> 19:30.190
So tell me, Robert,

19:30.190 --> 19:34.690
why am I holding a $100,000
off-the-books wire transfer

19:34.690 --> 19:36.320
with your name on it?

19:39.530 --> 19:43.950
Six months ago, I found out
all three name partners

19:43.950 --> 19:45.450
were laundering money.

19:45.450 --> 19:47.990
They offered to cut me in.
I said no.

19:47.990 --> 19:50.750
They put that money in there
to make me look complicit.

19:50.750 --> 19:52.250
Bullshit.
It's not bullshit.

19:52.250 --> 19:54.670
They wouldn't take the money
back, no matter what.

19:54.670 --> 19:57.250
So I did the next best thing
and gave it to charity.

19:57.250 --> 19:59.470
You don't believe me,
I'll show you the check.

19:59.470 --> 20:02.090
You can cut a check,
but can't blow the whistle.

20:02.090 --> 20:03.470
How noble.
It's complicated.

20:03.470 --> 20:05.010
It seems pretty simple to me.

20:05.010 --> 20:07.350
You witness a crime,
you tell the authorities.

20:07.350 --> 20:09.350
Which is what I'm gonna do
right now.

20:09.350 --> 20:12.600
ROBERT: Why don't you try telling
me that after you have a daughter?

20:12.600 --> 20:14.810
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:23.860 --> 20:25.280
Her name is Rachel.

20:28.160 --> 20:29.870
She wants to be a lawyer.

20:29.870 --> 20:34.250
How is that gonna go when she
applies to the bar and they say:

20:34.250 --> 20:36.040
"Isn't your father
a criminal?"

20:36.040 --> 20:37.460
You show them the check,

20:37.460 --> 20:39.670
and make them believe
you're not a criminal.

20:39.670 --> 20:41.970
This comes out,
my name is tainted forever.

20:44.180 --> 20:45.720
They'll never believe me.

20:45.720 --> 20:48.430
And if it was just me,
I'd take that chance.

20:48.430 --> 20:50.270
I'm sorry, Robert. It's...

20:50.270 --> 20:52.020
It's not my call.
Please!

20:52.020 --> 20:54.560
Now you came in here
because you wanted to hear

20:54.560 --> 20:56.100
my side of the story.

20:56.100 --> 21:00.990
My story is I'm a father
with a daughter.

21:04.320 --> 21:06.660
And I need your help.

21:14.790 --> 21:18.380
Samantha, I was wondering
when this visit was coming.

21:18.380 --> 21:20.250
What visit is that?
The one where you threaten me.

21:20.250 --> 21:23.170
I'm not here to threaten,
I'm here to offer you a way out

21:23.170 --> 21:24.420
before humiliating you,

21:24.420 --> 21:26.430
because you're still
a client of my firm.

21:26.430 --> 21:27.970
Get off my property.
I do that,

21:27.970 --> 21:30.180
the jury's gonna hear
from Phillip Jones.

21:30.180 --> 21:32.680
You thought you could
hide him from me.

21:32.680 --> 21:34.350
I don't know anyone
by that name.

21:34.350 --> 21:35.940
Funny, he has security footage

21:35.940 --> 21:37.270
showing you meeting with him

21:37.270 --> 21:39.520
two weeks before
you destroyed that painting.

21:39.520 --> 21:41.820
He'll never testify.
He already has.

21:41.820 --> 21:44.530
I have him under oath saying you
specifically asked him

21:44.530 --> 21:47.950
how much your Vermeer would go
up if another one got destroyed.

21:47.950 --> 21:50.660
I've got you, Gavin,
and I am not letting go.

21:50.660 --> 21:52.580
This is illegal
and inadmissible.

21:52.580 --> 21:55.500
You hacked my shit.
What I did was do to you

21:55.500 --> 21:57.670
what I used to do for you.

21:57.670 --> 22:00.420
And you can threaten me
or throw me off your property.

22:00.420 --> 22:02.090
But once we're in
that courtroom,

22:02.090 --> 22:04.170
I am not going anywhere.

22:06.800 --> 22:08.010
Give me a day.

22:09.390 --> 22:10.600
Excuse me?

22:10.600 --> 22:12.060
I'll pay what we owe.
I just...

22:12.060 --> 22:14.060
I need a day to get
the board's approval.

22:14.060 --> 22:16.060
No, I don't trust you.
You don't need to.

22:16.060 --> 22:18.600
You've got me,
like you just said.

22:18.600 --> 22:20.400
I'm still a client of the firm.

22:20.400 --> 22:22.110
That's gotta count
for something.

22:22.110 --> 22:24.150
It doesn't.
Samantha, please.

22:24.150 --> 22:26.360
You once told me
about your family.

22:26.360 --> 22:28.200
Well, I have a family, and...

22:29.240 --> 22:30.740
if this comes out,

22:30.740 --> 22:33.580
think about what
it's gonna do to my kids.

22:35.500 --> 22:37.040
One day.

22:37.870 --> 22:39.250
I'll give you one day,

22:39.250 --> 22:41.090
and then I'm putting you
on the stand.

22:41.090 --> 22:43.130
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:48.930 --> 22:50.510
KATRINA:
Louis, what's going on?

22:50.510 --> 22:52.050
What do you mean?

22:52.050 --> 22:54.560
I found a bouquet
of pink carnations on my desk.

22:54.560 --> 22:55.810
And since we both know

22:55.810 --> 22:57.390
that's the bouquet of apology,

22:57.390 --> 22:59.690
I thought I'd ask
what you're apologizing for.

22:59.690 --> 23:02.020
I wasn't apologizing to you.
I was to Sheila.

23:02.020 --> 23:03.900
Turns out,
she didn't want an apology.

23:03.900 --> 23:05.400
She wanted a change of heart.

23:05.400 --> 23:07.610
You just made
senior partner, so I thought,

23:07.610 --> 23:10.030
rather than throw them away...
Thank you, Louis.

23:10.030 --> 23:12.240
But I thought you and Sheila
were doing great.

23:12.240 --> 23:14.330
Yeah, we were,
until she got offered

23:14.330 --> 23:16.370
to be the dean
of Columbia Law School.

23:16.370 --> 23:18.040
And you're afraid
if she takes it,

23:18.040 --> 23:20.120
she won't have time for the baby.
Exactly.

23:20.120 --> 23:22.630
And with this added
responsibility, Katrina, I...

23:24.380 --> 23:26.460
I don't know
how it's gonna work.

23:28.970 --> 23:31.180
I know it's not my place,

23:31.180 --> 23:35.100
but did you consider
that if Sheila has less time,

23:35.100 --> 23:37.220
you might be able
to make more time?

23:37.220 --> 23:39.560
Katrina, I can't
just leave the firm.

23:39.560 --> 23:40.940
I know that, Louis.

23:40.940 --> 23:43.150
But three nights ago,
you came into my office

23:43.150 --> 23:44.770
and said you saw a look
on my face

23:44.770 --> 23:46.690
that you had seen
on yours before.

23:46.690 --> 23:49.650
Yes, the look of wishing for
someone to share your life with.

23:49.650 --> 23:51.740
You don't have
that look anymore.

23:51.740 --> 23:55.080
What you do have
is two name partners

23:55.080 --> 23:58.000
and a new senior partner
who have your back.

23:58.000 --> 23:59.830
Which means that
when the time comes,

23:59.830 --> 24:01.750
you'll be able to step back
a little

24:01.750 --> 24:05.460
and trust that the firm
is in good hands.

24:07.590 --> 24:10.130
Speaking of keeping the firm
in good hands, Katrina,

24:10.130 --> 24:11.720
I need to tell you something.

24:16.890 --> 24:19.520
What are you doing here?
We're due in court in an hour.

24:19.520 --> 24:21.350
No. Samantha
asked for a recess

24:21.350 --> 24:23.230
and got it.
What does she have now?

24:23.230 --> 24:25.650
It doesn't matter.
It matters what I have.

24:25.650 --> 24:27.690
What is that?
A list of ethical violations

24:27.690 --> 24:29.150
Samantha Wheeler engaged in

24:29.150 --> 24:31.320
over the course of six years
as my attorney.

24:31.320 --> 24:33.660
I'm not ruining her career.
You don't have to.

24:33.660 --> 24:36.160
You threaten to take this
to the bar, she'll cave.

24:36.160 --> 24:39.330
I'm not taking that chance. And
we don't need to. We're winning.

24:39.330 --> 24:41.750
No, Alex, we're not.

24:41.750 --> 24:43.170
What are you talking about?

24:43.170 --> 24:45.040
Samantha came to my house
this morning.

24:45.040 --> 24:47.670
She has proof I asked
an appraiser what would happen

24:47.670 --> 24:50.550
to the value of my Vermeer
if that painting got destroyed.

24:50.550 --> 24:52.630
If he gets on the stand...
Let me get this.

24:52.630 --> 24:54.970
There's a smoking gun,
and you kept it from me?

24:54.970 --> 24:56.800
You would have given it to her.

24:56.800 --> 24:58.760
All right, it's bad,
but it's not proof.

24:58.760 --> 25:01.390
We can cross-examine this...
Let me make myself clear.

25:01.390 --> 25:03.350
This is not a suggestion,
it is an order.

25:03.350 --> 25:04.940
If you don't use this, I will.

25:04.940 --> 25:06.900
And if I do it,
we're gonna skip the part

25:06.900 --> 25:08.860
where she gets the chance
to walk away,

25:08.860 --> 25:10.860
because I'll be going
straight to the bar.

25:10.860 --> 25:13.070
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:22.250 --> 25:23.960
I don't like that look
on your face.

25:23.960 --> 25:25.710
What look?
The look that says

25:25.710 --> 25:27.830
you're about to tell me
some serious shit.

25:27.830 --> 25:29.710
Samantha's got Gavin
by the balls,

25:29.710 --> 25:31.670
but I think I got a way out.

25:31.670 --> 25:33.300
How?
I did some digging.

25:33.300 --> 25:35.300
Dexhart has 80 percent
of the reinsurance

25:35.300 --> 25:36.550
for the packing company

25:36.550 --> 25:38.510
that should've protected
that painting.

25:38.510 --> 25:41.310
Meaning they'd have incentive
to clear them of any fault.

25:41.310 --> 25:43.060
Which they did
with a false report.

25:43.060 --> 25:45.190
You think Samantha's
hiding the real report?

25:45.190 --> 25:48.350
She's too smart to look at the
real report in the first place.

25:48.350 --> 25:49.980
If we ask for it
with a subpoena,

25:49.980 --> 25:51.650
it'll never see
the light of day.

25:51.650 --> 25:53.650
What exactly are you here
to ask me, Alex?

25:53.650 --> 25:55.280
Get Katrina Bennett to go there

25:55.280 --> 25:57.780
and ask for the unredacted
version of that report.

25:57.780 --> 25:59.280
No way.
Harvey.

25:59.280 --> 26:01.410
You're asking our lawyer
to commit a crime.

26:01.410 --> 26:03.410
It's not a crime.
She's a senior partner.

26:03.410 --> 26:05.870
All she has to do is say that,
ask for the files,

26:05.870 --> 26:07.500
and get out.
If it's so innocent,

26:07.500 --> 26:09.000
why don't you go do it yourself?

26:09.000 --> 26:11.380
No one's gonna mistake me
for Samantha Wheeler.

26:11.380 --> 26:13.170
Damn it.
You said you could beat her.

26:13.170 --> 26:15.170
I can.
This is what it's gonna take.

26:15.170 --> 26:17.880
I wouldn't be in this if you
didn't break your promise.

26:17.880 --> 26:19.800
That's bullshit.
You said you were good

26:19.800 --> 26:21.430
with fighting
to get your name up.

26:21.430 --> 26:23.640
What the hell
was I supposed to say?

26:26.940 --> 26:30.440
Alex, helping to speed up
the trial is one thing.

26:30.440 --> 26:32.650
Putting Katrina at risk?

26:32.650 --> 26:35.570
I'm not doing it.
Then you should know.

26:35.570 --> 26:38.400
I don't do this, Gavin Andrews
goes to the bar tomorrow

26:38.400 --> 26:41.330
with a list of shady things
Samantha's done over the years.

26:41.330 --> 26:43.080
So you can help me
with this or not.

26:43.080 --> 26:46.250
Either way, her name's
not going on that wall.

26:47.290 --> 26:49.500
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:54.670 --> 26:57.300
Katrina, if you're here
to go out for drinks tonight,

26:57.300 --> 27:00.890
I can only say that the answer
is a big, fat "Yes, please".

27:00.890 --> 27:03.430
As much as I would love
to say that's why I'm here,

27:03.430 --> 27:06.230
what I need is a big, fat
piece of advice.

27:06.230 --> 27:08.270
What is it?

27:08.270 --> 27:11.900
Harvey basically asked me
to impersonate Samantha Wheeler.

27:11.900 --> 27:13.610
What?

27:13.610 --> 27:16.650
It's the only way to get
what they need to help Alex win.

27:16.650 --> 27:18.610
What'd you tell him?

27:18.610 --> 27:20.950
I told him I didn't know.

27:20.950 --> 27:24.330
Well, if Harvey wants you
to do this, why not do it?

27:24.330 --> 27:27.410
Other than not wanting
to get on Samantha's bad side,

27:27.410 --> 27:31.120
Louis specifically told me
not to help either one of them.

27:31.120 --> 27:32.460
Did he say why?

27:32.460 --> 27:34.170
If too many people got involved,

27:34.170 --> 27:36.210
their fight could
tear the firm apart.

27:38.090 --> 27:42.640
Then I say too many people
are already involved.

27:42.640 --> 27:45.100
You might as well go ahead.
Help Harvey.

27:45.100 --> 27:46.930
Thanks, Donna.

27:47.810 --> 27:50.020
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:00.280 --> 28:02.910
What's this?
A settlement agreement.

28:02.910 --> 28:05.660
You're dropping that lawsuit,
paying Gavin's legal fees,

28:05.660 --> 28:07.950
and issuing a public apology.
The hell we are.

28:07.950 --> 28:10.290
Samantha, you can kick
and scream all you want,

28:10.290 --> 28:13.080
but I got proof the packing
company skimped on materials,

28:13.080 --> 28:14.710
and your client knew about it.

28:17.210 --> 28:18.710
How the fuck did you get these?

28:18.710 --> 28:20.170
Same way I got everything else.

28:20.170 --> 28:22.130
You shared it with me
in discovery.

28:22.130 --> 28:23.590
I didn't share shit with you.

28:23.590 --> 28:25.140
I never even saw
these documents.

28:25.140 --> 28:27.510
You never saw them because
you never wanted to.

28:27.510 --> 28:29.980
Dexhart Insurance has records
proving it was sent.

28:29.980 --> 28:32.270
You son of a bitch.
You cheated.

28:32.270 --> 28:35.190
No, I just played by
your rules. Don't start crying.

28:35.190 --> 28:37.150
I'm not crying,
and I'm not signing this.

28:37.150 --> 28:39.230
Let me tell you
what happens if you don't.

28:39.230 --> 28:41.150
Gavin Andrews
gets you disbarred.

28:41.150 --> 28:42.860
What?
He's got information

28:42.860 --> 28:44.860
that could end your career.
He told me to use it,

28:44.860 --> 28:47.490
but I didn't, because
I didn't wanna do that to you.

28:47.490 --> 28:49.870
So, what, I'm supposed
to thank you now?

28:49.870 --> 28:51.370
I don't expect you to thank me,

28:51.370 --> 28:53.250
but I expect you
to accept it's over.

28:53.250 --> 28:55.080
I'm not accepting anything.
I get it.

28:55.080 --> 28:56.420
You're not used to losing.

28:56.420 --> 28:58.590
But whether you want
to admit it or not...

28:58.590 --> 29:00.260
I won, you lost.

29:00.260 --> 29:01.800
And come tomorrow,

29:01.800 --> 29:04.010
my name's going up on that wall.

29:05.680 --> 29:07.890
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:16.360 --> 29:18.690
Louis, what are you doing here?

29:18.690 --> 29:21.400
Not bringing flowers,
if that's what you're wondering.

29:21.400 --> 29:23.110
Sheila, the reason
I was so thrown

29:23.110 --> 29:25.030
with you taking on
more responsibility

29:25.030 --> 29:28.200
was because I was afraid

29:28.200 --> 29:30.370
that I wouldn't be able
to take on less.

29:30.370 --> 29:33.210
Whether you are offered
the permanent position or not,

29:33.210 --> 29:34.370
when the time comes,

29:34.370 --> 29:36.460
I wanna take time
for our family.

29:36.460 --> 29:40.090
Well, I'm... I'm glad
to hear you say that.

29:42.460 --> 29:44.550
Because the time has come.

29:44.550 --> 29:47.090
You mean, you were offered
the permanent position?

29:47.090 --> 29:48.590
No, not that time, Louis.

29:50.100 --> 29:51.720
The other time.

29:51.720 --> 29:54.430
Oh, my God.

29:54.430 --> 29:56.850
Are you saying
what I think you're saying?

29:56.850 --> 29:58.650
I saw Chaz this afternoon.

29:58.650 --> 30:01.360
And we're not going to need
that surgery, because...

30:02.650 --> 30:04.740
we're gonna have a baby.

30:04.740 --> 30:07.610
I don't believe this.
Are you sure?

30:07.610 --> 30:09.370
I mean...

30:10.330 --> 30:12.580
are you absolutely sure?

30:12.580 --> 30:14.200
Yes. I'm positive.

30:14.200 --> 30:16.040
And I'm sorry we fought.

30:17.080 --> 30:19.540
I just...
I'm stressed,

30:19.540 --> 30:22.300
and I've got hormones
running through me,

30:22.300 --> 30:25.090
and I'm not even sure if
I want that permanent position.

30:25.090 --> 30:26.430
Hey. It's okay.

30:27.430 --> 30:29.680
It's all gonna be okay.

30:29.680 --> 30:33.140
I am right here by your side,
and I'm not going anywhere.

30:33.140 --> 30:34.560
How are you so calm?

30:34.560 --> 30:37.310
Because I know
what's important now.

30:37.310 --> 30:39.190
And it's this.

30:41.060 --> 30:42.980
Everything's gonna be okay.

30:42.980 --> 30:44.530
Okay.

30:46.450 --> 30:48.650
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:53.660 --> 30:56.250
I got your message.
You're late.

30:56.250 --> 30:58.210
I had some thinking to do.

30:58.210 --> 30:59.870
Well, I'm glad you showed up.

30:59.870 --> 31:02.130
I was beginning to wonder
if I was meeting you

31:02.130 --> 31:03.590
or the feds in here tonight.

31:03.590 --> 31:05.840
I think I have a way
to get you out of this.

31:05.840 --> 31:08.090
You mind if I ask you
what changed your mind?

31:08.090 --> 31:09.930
Because I believe you.

31:09.930 --> 31:13.010
I also know if I do this for
you, you'll always have my back.

31:13.010 --> 31:14.310
You're saying I owe you?

31:14.310 --> 31:16.180
I'm saying you'll feel grateful.

31:16.180 --> 31:18.140
It isn't the same thing.

31:18.140 --> 31:19.850
No, it's not.

31:19.850 --> 31:21.350
So, what's your plan?

31:21.350 --> 31:23.610
Who here do you trust
more than anyone else?

31:23.610 --> 31:25.360
[LAUGHS]
After tonight? That's easy.

31:25.360 --> 31:27.240
You.
No. It can't be me.

31:27.240 --> 31:29.950
Raises too many red flags.
Besides, I'm not old enough.

31:29.950 --> 31:32.620
It's not my time.
What are you talking about?

31:32.620 --> 31:33.950
Just answer the question.

31:33.950 --> 31:36.080
You need somebody here
to have your back.

31:36.080 --> 31:37.370
It isn't me. Who is it?

31:37.370 --> 31:39.120
Two people.

31:41.120 --> 31:43.630
Ellen Rand and Eric Kaldor.

31:43.630 --> 31:45.130
Then get them,

31:45.130 --> 31:47.380
'cause we're not
out of the woods yet.

31:47.380 --> 31:49.420
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:55.890 --> 31:58.390
It's good that you reached out
to me when you did.

31:58.390 --> 32:00.940
I was starting to think
you made a wrong choice.

32:00.940 --> 32:03.060
I've made enough wrong
choices in my life.

32:03.060 --> 32:05.020
I'm not gonna make
a wrong one on this.

32:05.020 --> 32:06.730
So, what'd you find?
Nothing.

32:06.730 --> 32:09.070
All I found was a glitch
in the billing system.

32:09.070 --> 32:12.070
Bullshit. We got information...
I don't care what you've got.

32:12.070 --> 32:14.200
Clients were overcharged,
then reimbursed.

32:14.200 --> 32:15.450
That's all there was to it.

32:15.450 --> 32:17.200
When I subpoena
every billing record

32:17.200 --> 32:19.700
from the last five years,
that's never gonna hold.

32:19.700 --> 32:22.750
If you could've subpoenaed them,
you wouldn't have come to me.

32:22.750 --> 32:25.540
I get it.
They paid you off,

32:25.540 --> 32:27.380
and now you're as guilty
as they are.

32:27.380 --> 32:30.010
Don't you say that to me.
You tried to use my history

32:30.010 --> 32:31.510
to get me to turn on my family.

32:31.510 --> 32:33.720
If you unseal my records,
I guarantee you

32:33.720 --> 32:35.260
the firm of Rand Kaldor Zane

32:35.260 --> 32:37.810
will use every resource
they have to come after you

32:37.810 --> 32:39.270
for malicious prosecution.

32:39.270 --> 32:41.640
Rand Kaldor Zane?
That's right.

32:41.640 --> 32:43.770
Jarvis, Ellis, and Green
are stepping down.

32:43.770 --> 32:45.860
So if you're convinced
they did something,

32:45.860 --> 32:48.860
think of it as a punishment
getting served after all.

32:48.860 --> 32:51.070
That's not punishment,
that's getting away.

32:51.070 --> 32:53.490
If you think having your name
ripped off the wall

32:53.490 --> 32:55.490
you worked your entire life to
get up there isn't punishment,

32:55.490 --> 32:57.450
you don't know what it is
to be a lawyer.

32:57.450 --> 32:59.870
Because, trust me,
it's all any of us ever want.

32:59.870 --> 33:01.710
Why didn't you put
your name there?

33:01.710 --> 33:03.160
Because it's not my time, Tom.

33:03.160 --> 33:05.250
But you can bet your ass
someday it will be.

33:05.250 --> 33:07.460
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:13.170 --> 33:15.050
ROBERT:
Samantha.

33:15.050 --> 33:17.300
You here to tell me you won?

33:18.800 --> 33:21.220
I'm here to tell you
Alex has a smoking gun,

33:21.220 --> 33:22.810
and he's got me dead to rights.

33:22.810 --> 33:24.560
What?

33:24.560 --> 33:26.480
I lost, Robert.

33:27.980 --> 33:29.320
It's over.

33:30.820 --> 33:32.320
How the hell did that happen?

33:32.320 --> 33:33.530
I had him.

33:33.530 --> 33:36.360
I had my foot on Gavin's neck.

33:37.530 --> 33:39.580
I gave him extra time.

33:39.580 --> 33:42.870
And I'm not gonna lose
what's mine

33:42.870 --> 33:45.750
because Alex used that time
to win.

33:45.750 --> 33:47.080
What are you saying?

33:47.080 --> 33:48.880
I don't give a shit
what the agreement was.

33:48.880 --> 33:51.050
My name's going on that wall,
make it happen.

33:51.050 --> 33:52.550
I can't do that.
Why not?

33:52.550 --> 33:54.470
Samantha.
Goddamn it, Robert!

33:54.470 --> 33:55.970
They found those files,

33:55.970 --> 33:58.180
which means you didn't
tip the scales at all.

33:58.180 --> 34:01.100
What is it gonna take for you
to get off the sidelines?

34:01.100 --> 34:03.060
I wouldn't have
to get off the sidelines

34:03.060 --> 34:05.180
if you hadn't shown
Gavin Andrews mercy.

34:05.180 --> 34:07.350
I didn't just do that
because he's a client,

34:07.350 --> 34:09.560
I did it because
he told me he had a family.

34:09.560 --> 34:11.480
Just like you once did.

34:11.480 --> 34:13.690
You're saying I owe you.

34:13.690 --> 34:16.400
You have owed me for years,
and you know it.

34:17.820 --> 34:19.870
And before
you gave them your word,

34:19.870 --> 34:22.080
you gave your word to me.

34:22.080 --> 34:27.000
So the question is, which word
are you gonna live up to?

34:27.000 --> 34:29.170
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:38.429 --> 34:40.850
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

34:46.770 --> 34:48.980
Louis, we need to talk.
It's important.

34:48.980 --> 34:51.060
Yeah, of course.
Come in.

34:52.520 --> 34:54.900
Actually, I'm glad you're here,

34:54.900 --> 34:56.400
'cause I have news of my own.

34:56.400 --> 34:58.400
Whatever it is,
it's not as big as this.

34:58.400 --> 35:00.200
Robert's about to tell Harvey

35:00.200 --> 35:02.450
he's gonna put up Samantha's
name instead of Alex's.

35:02.450 --> 35:04.540
No. Alex won.
Robert can't break his word.

35:04.540 --> 35:06.580
He's going to.
If we don't do something,

35:06.580 --> 35:07.910
we're not gonna have a firm,

35:07.910 --> 35:10.120
we're gonna have a war
on our hands.

35:10.120 --> 35:12.170
Okay. I hear you.
First thing tomorrow,

35:12.170 --> 35:14.880
we'll get in a conference room
and talk this through.

35:14.880 --> 35:18.880
It's too late for that.
The time for talking is over.

35:18.880 --> 35:20.590
We need to do something.

35:21.890 --> 35:23.810
And that something is...

35:23.810 --> 35:26.970
I'll step down.
What?

35:26.970 --> 35:31.230
Donna, Sheila's pregnant.
I'm gonna be a father.

35:31.230 --> 35:32.480
Oh, my God.

35:32.480 --> 35:34.070
I was gonna ratchet down,
anyway.

35:34.070 --> 35:36.530
This way, they can both
put their names up.

35:36.530 --> 35:39.610
Louis, I am so happy for you.

35:40.860 --> 35:42.370
But that's not gonna work.

35:42.370 --> 35:43.870
What are you saying?
I'm saying

35:43.870 --> 35:45.990
you need to step in
as managing partner.

35:47.250 --> 35:48.750
What?
Louis,

35:48.750 --> 35:50.830
Robert can't run
this firm right now,

35:50.830 --> 35:52.120
and neither can Harvey.

35:52.120 --> 35:53.500
You're the only one who can.

35:53.500 --> 35:54.840
Sorry, Donna. I can't.

35:54.840 --> 35:57.090
Why not?
Because I'm not a leader.

35:57.090 --> 35:58.630
They won't follow me.

35:58.630 --> 35:59.920
Louis.

36:01.300 --> 36:03.680
I know you went to Katrina
to protect the firm,

36:03.680 --> 36:06.470
and you just offered to step
down to do the same thing.

36:06.470 --> 36:08.850
If that's not the leadership
we need right now,

36:08.850 --> 36:10.100
I don't know what is.

36:10.100 --> 36:12.400
Why does it have to be now?

36:12.400 --> 36:14.900
I just wanna be a father.
And the last thing

36:14.900 --> 36:17.400
I'd ever wanna do
is take that away from you.

36:17.400 --> 36:20.490
But your baby's not due
for another nine months.

36:20.490 --> 36:24.320
And this firm is your baby too.
And it needs you right now.

36:24.320 --> 36:28.410
I can't make that decision
without talking to Sheila first.

36:28.410 --> 36:30.410
Then hurry.

36:30.410 --> 36:32.250
Because we don't have
a lot of time.

36:32.250 --> 36:34.290
Donna.

36:34.290 --> 36:37.550
Even if I said yes,

36:37.550 --> 36:40.050
Harvey and Robert
would never vote

36:40.050 --> 36:42.170
to make me managing partner.

36:42.170 --> 36:44.260
You leave that to me.

36:45.220 --> 36:47.430
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:59.730 --> 37:01.610
I take it you're celebrating.

37:03.110 --> 37:04.820
It's a drink, Robert.

37:04.820 --> 37:08.700
I'm not rubbing it
in anybody's face, but yeah.

37:08.700 --> 37:10.950
I'm happy for my guy.

37:10.950 --> 37:13.710
Well, I'm here to say something

37:13.710 --> 37:16.170
that's gonna make you
less happy.

37:16.170 --> 37:18.340
What's that?

37:18.340 --> 37:21.300
I'm putting Samantha's name
on the wall, not Alex's.

37:21.300 --> 37:22.630
[SCOFFS]

37:22.630 --> 37:24.050
I must be getting old,

37:24.050 --> 37:27.220
because I'm pretty sure
I just heard you say

37:27.220 --> 37:28.810
you're breaking your word.

37:28.810 --> 37:31.350
I know. I promised.
You didn't just make a promise.

37:31.350 --> 37:33.140
You looked me in the eye
and said,

37:33.140 --> 37:35.940
"Let's settle this in the ring."
I don't care. I owe her.

37:35.940 --> 37:37.900
You should've
put her name up years ago,

37:37.900 --> 37:39.360
not when it costs someone else.

37:39.360 --> 37:41.360
I am the managing partner
of this firm.

37:41.360 --> 37:42.740
We can change that right now,

37:42.740 --> 37:44.360
because I was here before you,

37:44.360 --> 37:46.950
and I'm gonna be here
long after you're gone.

37:46.950 --> 37:49.370
Are you threatening me?
I'm giving you a choice.

37:49.370 --> 37:52.580
You and Samantha can accept
Alex, or you can pack up now.

37:52.580 --> 37:54.290
I'm not going.
Neither is Samantha.

37:54.290 --> 37:56.500
You're the past
and she's the future.

37:56.500 --> 37:58.960
Not here, she's not.
Get the fuck out of my office.

37:58.960 --> 38:01.420
That's enough.
No one's going anywhere,

38:01.420 --> 38:04.010
and neither one of you
is managing partner anymore.

38:04.010 --> 38:06.380
Stay out of this.
No, I'm putting a stop to this,

38:06.380 --> 38:08.300
and I'm putting a stop to it
right now.

38:08.300 --> 38:10.850
'Cause this isn't just
a friendly gathering.

38:10.850 --> 38:12.430
This is
a formal partner meeting.

38:12.430 --> 38:14.100
And here's how it's gonna go.

38:14.100 --> 38:16.140
I'm voting for Louis
for managing partner,

38:16.140 --> 38:17.650
and he's voting for himself.

38:17.650 --> 38:19.900
Since there's no way
that either one of you

38:19.900 --> 38:21.110
is voting for the other,

38:21.110 --> 38:22.860
you might as well
both vote for him

38:22.860 --> 38:24.440
and keep this a united front.

38:24.440 --> 38:27.610
Because make no mistake,
Louis is managing partner.

38:27.610 --> 38:30.070
Bullshit. There's no way
you're pulling this off.

38:30.070 --> 38:32.080
She's not pulling this off,
Robert. I am.

38:32.080 --> 38:33.790
This is happening,
like it or not.

38:33.790 --> 38:36.210
You think you have what it
takes to run this firm?

38:36.210 --> 38:38.620
I know I do.
And my first order of business

38:38.620 --> 38:41.000
is promoting Alex and Samantha
at the same time.

38:41.000 --> 38:42.750
Any managing partner worth his salt

38:42.750 --> 38:44.260
can see they'll never go for it.

38:44.260 --> 38:46.130
They're either both gonna accept this,

38:46.130 --> 38:49.220
or they're both out the door,
because I am sick of this shit.

38:49.220 --> 38:50.930
And I'll tell you something else.

38:50.930 --> 38:54.220
You two are gonna goddamn
sell it to them.

38:56.480 --> 38:57.980
DONNA: So, what's it gonna be?

38:57.980 --> 38:59.810
Me and Louis and a split decision,

38:59.810 --> 39:02.570
or are we gonna make this thing unanimous?

39:02.570 --> 39:04.780
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:13.410 --> 39:17.000
How'd they take it?
Kicking and screaming.

39:17.000 --> 39:18.920
Bet you wouldn't have it any other way.

39:18.920 --> 39:21.210
Nope, I wouldn't.

39:21.210 --> 39:23.670
What'd you tell Rand and Kaldor?

39:25.170 --> 39:28.670
That all they had to do
was be ready to act in charge,

39:28.670 --> 39:30.760
and I could get them the firm.

39:30.760 --> 39:32.260
And let me guess.

39:32.260 --> 39:35.180
They knew not to ask
any more questions than that.

39:35.180 --> 39:38.640
Isn't that what being a great
lawyer's all about?

39:38.640 --> 39:40.190
Sometimes.

39:40.190 --> 39:43.060
Sometimes it's about asking
the right questions.

39:43.060 --> 39:45.650
Okay, then.

39:45.650 --> 39:47.280
Why'd you do it?

39:47.280 --> 39:49.990
Do what?
Help me.

39:49.990 --> 39:53.160
And don't give me that line
about always having your back,

39:53.160 --> 39:56.490
because it's gotta be about
something more.

39:58.160 --> 39:59.750
I didn't have a father.

39:59.750 --> 40:01.500
What?

40:01.500 --> 40:03.420
I... I have no idea
who my parents were.

40:03.420 --> 40:06.090
Didn't even know their names.

40:06.090 --> 40:07.460
[SIGHS]

40:07.460 --> 40:09.760
I bounced around
the foster care system.

40:09.760 --> 40:13.010
Never lived in the same place
for more than two years.

40:13.010 --> 40:16.390
What does that have to do with...
Your daughter.

40:16.390 --> 40:20.350
I helped you because
I would have given anything

40:20.350 --> 40:22.730
to have someone like you
looking out for me.

40:24.310 --> 40:26.980
And I didn't wanna
take it away from her.

40:26.980 --> 40:29.110
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:29.110 --> 40:31.150
[SIGHS]

40:32.530 --> 40:34.700
I don't know what to say.

40:34.700 --> 40:36.370
Say that from now on,

40:36.370 --> 40:39.450
I'll always have someone
looking out for me.

40:45.040 --> 40:47.290
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

40:49.170 --> 40:51.170
Robert.
Samantha, have a seat.

40:51.170 --> 40:54.300
I don't want one unless you're
saying it's a seat at the table.

40:54.300 --> 40:55.390
It is.

40:56.510 --> 40:58.560
But you're not alone.

40:58.560 --> 41:00.390
Alex is getting a promotion too.

41:00.390 --> 41:01.810
Are you kidding me?

41:01.810 --> 41:03.900
The whole point
